# StockArb job schedule, run by supercronic (PID 1).
# All times are America/New_York local time — CRON_TZ handles DST
# automatically via the container's tzdata package.
#
# Format: CRON_TZ=<tz> MIN HOUR DOM MON DOW COMMAND
# supercronic streams each job's stdout/stderr directly to the container's
# stdout, so `docker logs -f` shows everything with no extra log files.

# 1) Data pipeline — 18:00 ET, Mon-Fri (well after the 16:00 ET market close,
#    gives Yahoo Finance time to finalize the day's adjusted close).
CRON_TZ=America/New_York 0 18 * * 1-5 python -m app.run_data_pipeline

# 2) Analytics engine (cointegration screen + rolling z-scores) — 18:30 ET,
#    Mon-Fri. 30-minute buffer after the data pipeline is comfortably enough
#    for a ~100-pair Engle-Granger screen.
CRON_TZ=America/New_York 30 18 * * 1-5 python -m app.run_analytics

# 3) Execution engine — every 15 minutes, 09:00-16:00 ET, Mon-Fri. Runs
#    outside 09:30-16:00 regular hours are cheap no-ops (the engine checks
#    Alpaca's market clock and exits immediately if closed).
CRON_TZ=America/New_York */15 9-16 * * 1-5 python -m app.run_execution
